cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.SI. 

The paper introduces new data structures for answering connectivity queries in graphs subject to batched vertex failures, which is a problem in graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also presents a new decomposition theorem for undirected graphs, which is related to graph theory and combinatorics, suggesting that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another likely category. The paper involves designing efficient algorithms for graphs, which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category. The paper also involves analyzing the time and space complexity of the proposed algorithms, which suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also possible categories.
